      "SummaryText": "Thatcher Company is a leader in the water purification chemical industry manufactures and distributes environmental chemicals for the municipal, agricultural, mining, and industrial markets. TCSLC is a member of the National Association of Chemical Distributors and has been certified to be in compliance with the Responsible Distribution Code. The company is also an active member of the Chlorine Institute, a trade group that develops and establishes recommended practices for the safe handling of chlorine. The TCSLC facility is a repackager, manufacturer and distributor of various industrial chemicals. Major markets include drinking water treatment, wastewater treatment, industrial applications, agriculture, and food processing. Chlorine, sulfur dioxide, and ammonia (including mixtures and byproducts) are distributed to the water treatment, wastewater treatment, agriculture and industrial markets. Thatcher Group states in its EHS Charter that the Environmental, Health, Safety, and Security Mission is to achieve a manufacturing environment that we are proud of by continuously improving our ability to provide our customers with quality products and services that meet their needs while operating with the highest standards of safety and environmental compliance. To operate with the highest standards of safety and environmental compliance, our commitment to EHS must include: compliance with work instructions and procedures; clear expectations; a constant focus on prevention; active participation; awareness on and off the job; strong leadership; and personal responsibility. Further, a commitment to EHS must include personal accountability for their EHS performance and for the EHS performance of those they manage or supervise.\n \nIn addition to EPA's RMP rule, the Thatcher Company complies with State and Federal OSHA's Process Safety Management, EPA's State and Federal Hazardous Waste Generator, DHS's Chemical Facility Anti-Terrorism Standard and DOT's Pipeline and Hazardous"
